Source: wlanpi-desktop
Section: x11
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Josh Schmelzle <josh@joshschmelzle.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 10)
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://github.com/WLAN-Pi/wlanpi-desktop

Package: wlanpi-desktop
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         openbox,
         lxpanel,
         lightdm,
         lightdm-gtk-greeter,
         xfce4-terminal,
         firefox-esr,
         pcmanfm,
         network-manager-gnome,
         xdg-utils,
         libnss3-tools,
         systemd,
         x11-xserver-utils
Description: Minimal desktop environment for WLAN Pi
 wlanpi-desktop provides a lightweight, on-demand desktop environment
 optimized for single-board computers like Raspberry Pi.
 .
 Features:
  - Disabled by default
  - Openbox window manager with LXPanel
  - Simple management via wlanpi-gui command
  - Autologin support (disabled by default)
  - Configurable screen blanking (10 min default)
  - Firefox ESR
